snippet.title: Anulom Vilom Pranayam Yoga Breathing Meditation - Day 20
snippet.description:
The Yoga breathing exercise Anulom Vilom Pranayam, is one type of pranayama, and is great for beginners, as it is simple but very powerful. The Yoga breathing technique pranayam, means extension of the breath, and the anulom vilom pranayam yogic exercise has great benefits and a strong effect on increasing your lung capacity, your respiratory system, your circulatory system and can help boost your metabolism and helps you lose weight, as a yoga for weight loss. The pranayama techniques are used in yoga and if you want some easy yoga exercises for beginners, why not start with the central part of the breath, to restore your health and give you inner peace. 
Anulom vilom pranayam, also known as Alternate Nostril Breathing, is great for people who suffer from asthma or anxiety, as it help you breathe and clears your airway to better obtain oxygen. In Anulom Vilom Pranayam, you will inhale and exhale through only one nostril at the time, switching between the right and the left. This guided meditation video, will help you through the meditation exercise, and if therefore great for beginners.

IMPORTANT: if you feel any dizziness or discomfort, adjust the speed and the length of the inhalations and exhalations, or take a break.

snippet.title: Zen Meditation Zazen and Kinhin Walking Meditation - Day 30
snippet.description:
Guided relaxing Zen meditation Zazen followed by the Buddhist walking meditation Kinhin for enlightenment and inner awareness. Zen meditation or Zazen is an ancient Buddhism meditation practice, that means seated meditation, and allows you to empty your mind and find inner peace and awareness. Walking meditation can be a great break from seated meditation, but is also a integrated part of the Zen meditation, as it allows for another experience and another way of achieving inner peace, enlightenment and awareness. This is a guided zen meditation that last 30 minutes, and will take you through the exercise. In the zen meditation Zazen you will sit in either full, half lotus or burmese meditation posture with your hands in the cosmic mudra breathing into your hara. For the Kinhin walking meditation, your hands will be in the Shashu mudra and you will walk clockwise taking one half step for each exhalation. So try this Zen meditation and walking meditation to learn how to relax. There will be soothing and relaxing water sounds in the background to help you relax and connect with the nature.

This is the last day of the 30 day meditation challenge for beginners. Congratulation! you have now finished this 30 day challenge which is a great step, as the hardest part is often to get started with meditation. Hope it has been a great experience and that it has taught you how to meditate.

The 7 Steps to Happiness Challenge... Only available on Patreon!

Welcome to the 7 Step to Happiness Challenge… the video course that will help you step outside your comfort zone and change your life from being fine into being extraordinary. If you feel stuck in the same boring routine, working on autopilot most of the time, feeling unfulfilled and low on energy, motivation and excitement, then this challenge will help you turn your life around… giving you new motivation and a passion for life, and giving you a sense of inner peace and happiness.

Life is supposed to be an adventure, but most of us get stuck at some point, doing things that do not excite us… stuck in a mundane life, where every day look exactly alike. We lose our passion for life and wonder how we will ever get this passion back. But it is much easier than you may think. The key is to do a little each day to pull us out of this autopilot mode, and allow us to appreciate all the wonderful things we have in our lives, plus setting new exciting goals and work towards those. This challenge will give you 7 steps, each with at least 2 exercises to help turn your life into an adventure, and help you let go of regret, hurt and self-blame, so that you can step into your new life and experience happiness once again.

This challenge consists of 28 videos, and twice a week, Mondays and Fridays, you will get a new video with a new challenge or inspiration to bring you towards your goal.
